{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabInstanceWanted\"><span class=\"name\">elabInstanceWanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab\">Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Parses the surface syntax of `instance_wanted`, generates a name if absent, forwards to the\nshared `elabWanted`, validates the payload is a typeclass, and registers the declared name in\n`wantedInstancesExt` so subsequent wanted declarations auto-include it. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabInstanceWanted","kind":"def","line":528,"name":"elabInstanceWanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L528-L551"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#instance_wanted\"><span class=\"name\">instance_wanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Parser/Types.html#Lean.Parser.Parser\">Lean.Parser.Parser</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This typeclass instance would be a welcome contribution to the library!\n\nThe syntax mirrors `instance` (the name is optional, auto-generated from the class head if\nabsent) and the payload must be a typeclass. The placeholder is recorded as\n`DefWanted (TheClass …)` like `def_wanted`, but additionally the declared\nname is registered so every subsequent `theorem_wanted` / `def_wanted` /\n`instance_wanted` automatically picks up a `[d_…]` instance binder for it. Lean's typeclass\nsynth then resolves uses of the class without an explicit `❰…❱` reference — matching the\nauto-availability of regular `instance` declarations.\n\nThe registration is **module-scoped and order-sensitive**: every `instance_wanted` declared\nearlier in the current file is auto-included as a binder on every later wanted declaration\n(without any class-name filtering — opting in via `instance_wanted` is taken as a request for\nthe instance to be ambient). Registrations persist across `section` / `namespace` boundaries\nwithin the file and are dropped at module boundaries (the placeholder defs are `private`, so\nnothing propagates to importers).\n\nTypical usage:\n```\ndef_wanted Jacobian (C : Over (Spec (.of k))) [IsProper C.hom] : Over (Spec (.of k))\n\ninstance_wanted : GrpObj (❰Jacobian❱ C)\n\ntheorem_wanted comp_ofCurve … : … = η[❰Jacobian❱ C]\n  -- automatically picks up the GrpObj instance, no haveI needed\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#instance_wanted","kind":"def","line":464,"name":"instance_wanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L464-L496"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabDefWanted\"><span class=\"name\">elabDefWanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab\">Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Parses the surface syntax of `def_wanted` and forwards to the shared `elabWanted`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabDefWanted","kind":"def","line":456,"name":"elabDefWanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L456-L462"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabProofWanted\"><span class=\"name\">elabProofWanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab\">Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Parses the surface syntax of `proof_wanted` (a synonym for `theorem_wanted`) and forwards to\nthe shared `elabWanted`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabProofWanted","kind":"def","line":447,"name":"elabProofWanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L447-L454"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabTheoremWanted\"><span class=\"name\">elabTheoremWanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab\">Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElab</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Parses the surface syntax of `theorem_wanted` and forwards to the shared `elabWanted`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabTheoremWanted","kind":"def","line":439,"name":"elabTheoremWanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L439-L445"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#def_wanted\"><span class=\"name\">def_wanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Parser/Types.html#Lean.Parser.Parser\">Lean.Parser.Parser</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This construction would be a welcome contribution to the library!\n\nThe syntax mirrors `theorem_wanted` but admits any `Sort` (not just `Prop`). It records a\nplaceholder declaration of type `... → DefWanted type` and accepts the same `❰…❱`\nbracket syntax for cross-referencing earlier `theorem_wanted` or `def_wanted`\ndeclarations, including parametrised ones — `❰foo❱ x y` applies `foo`'s parameters. A partial\nbody may be supplied with `... := body`; as with `theorem_wanted`, a body without any `❰…❱`\nreference is rejected with an actionable \"Try this:\" suggesting `def`.\n\nModifiers (such as `@[simp]`) are accepted for syntactic compatibility with `def` but are\ncurrently ignored.\n\nTypical usage:\n```\ndef_wanted decision_procedure (n : Nat) : Decidable (Nat.Prime n)\n\ndef_wanted prime_dec_3 : Decidable (Nat.Prime 3) := ❰decision_procedure❱ 3\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#def_wanted","kind":"def","line":414,"name":"def_wanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L414-L437"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#proof_wanted\"><span class=\"name\">proof_wanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Parser/Types.html#Lean.Parser.Parser\">Lean.Parser.Parser</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`proof_wanted` is a synonym for `theorem_wanted`; see its documentation. (It is expected to be\ndeprecated in favour of `theorem_wanted` eventually.) ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#proof_wanted","kind":"def","line":406,"name":"proof_wanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L406-L412"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#theorem_wanted\"><span class=\"name\">theorem_wanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Parser/Types.html#Lean.Parser.Parser\">Lean.Parser.Parser</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"This proof would be a welcome contribution to the library!\n\nThe syntax of `theorem_wanted` declarations is just like that of `theorem`. Without `:=` and a\nproof body it records a wanted theorem; with one it records a partial proof that still depends on\nother wanted lemmas. Lean checks that `theorem_wanted` declarations are well-formed (e.g. it\nensures that all the mentioned names are in scope, and that the theorem statement is a valid\nproposition), and records a private placeholder declaration of type `... → ProofWanted statement`.\n\nModifiers (such as `@[simp]`) are accepted for syntactic compatibility with `theorem` but are\ncurrently ignored.\n\n`proof_wanted` is a synonym for `theorem_wanted`.\n\nInside another `theorem_wanted` or `def_wanted`, write `❰foo❱` to reference an earlier\n`theorem_wanted` or `def_wanted` named `foo`. The bracket may appear in the statement or\nthe body, and each distinct reference becomes a fresh parameter binder of the matching type. For\nparametrised `foo : ∀ args, ProofWanted _`, the binder type is itself Π-quantified, so `❰foo❱ x\ny` applies the parameter to `x y`. `❰foo❱` only resolves names within the current file, since\nthe placeholders are `private`.\n\nA body must reference at least one `❰…❱` (in the statement or the body); otherwise the body is\na complete proof and the declaration should be a `theorem`.\n\nTypical usage:\n```\n-- A parameterless wanted fact:\ntheorem_wanted size_of_two_pushes_onto_empty :\n    ((#[] : Array Nat).push 1 |>.push 2).size = 2\n\n-- Referencing an earlier `theorem_wanted` inside a statement (here in the `Fin`\n-- bound proof, which rewrites by the wanted fact):\ntheorem_wanted first_index_after_two_pushes :\n    (⟨0, by rw [❰size_of_two_pushes_onto_empty❱]; decide⟩\n      : Fin ((#[] : Array Nat).push 1 |>.push 2).size).val = 0\n\n-- A parametrised wanted fact:\ntheorem_wanted size_after_two_pushes {α : Type _} (a : Array α) (x y : α) :\n    ((a.push x).push y).size = a.size + 2\n\n-- Referencing the parametrised wanted with arguments: `❰foo❱ a x y`.\ntheorem_wanted index_after_two_pushes {α : Type _} (a : Array α) (x y : α) :\n    (⟨a.size, by rw [❰size_after_two_pushes❱ a x y]; omega⟩\n      : Fin ((a.push x).push y).size).val = a.size\n\n-- A partial proof may be supplied with `:= body`, deferring the harder step via `❰…❱`:\ntheorem_wanted size_after_three_pushes {α : Type _} (a : Array α) (x y z : α) :\n    (((a.push x).push y).push z).size = a.size + 3 := by\n  rw [Array.size_push, ❰size_after_two_pushes❱ a x y]\n```\n","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#theorem_wanted","kind":"def","line":350,"name":"theorem_wanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L350-L404"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabWantedRef\"><span class=\"name\">elabWantedRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElab\">Lean.Elab.Term.TermElab</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Elaborator that errors when `❰…❱` is used outside a wanted-declaration command. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#elabWantedRef","kind":"def","line":70,"name":"elabWantedRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L70-L74"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#wantedRef\"><span class=\"name\">wantedRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">Lean.ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Internal bracket syntax `❰foo❱` for referencing an earlier `theorem_wanted` or\n`def_wanted`. Only meaningful inside the statement or body of one of those commands;\nthe term elaborator errors everywhere else. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#wantedRef","kind":"def","line":65,"name":"wantedRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L65-L68"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted.Val\"><span class=\"name\">DefWanted</span>.<span class=\"name\">Val</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted\">DefWanted</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Reducible accessor so a binder of type `DefWanted.Val foo` reduces to `foo`'s\ntype. Used by the desugaring of `❰foo❱` when `foo` is a `def_wanted`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted.Val","kind":"def","line":56,"name":"DefWanted.Val","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L56-L59"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted.mk\"><span class=\"name\">DefWanted</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u} → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted\">DefWanted</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The trivial constructor; carries no information. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted.mk","kind":"ctor","line":51,"name":"DefWanted.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L51-L54"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted\"><span class=\"name\">DefWanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Wrapper recording that a `def_wanted` of type `α` has been declared. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#DefWanted","kind":"structure","line":51,"name":"DefWanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L51-L54"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted.Stmt\"><span class=\"name\">ProofWanted</span>.<span class=\"name\">Stmt</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted\">ProofWanted</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span> → <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Reducible accessor so a binder of type `ProofWanted.Stmt foo` reduces to `foo`'s\nstatement. Used by the desugaring of `❰foo❱` when `foo` is a `proof_wanted`. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted.Stmt","kind":"def","line":46,"name":"ProofWanted.Stmt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L46-L49"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">constructor</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted.mk\"><span class=\"name\">ProofWanted</span>.<span class=\"name\">mk</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u} → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted\">ProofWanted</a> <span class=\"fn\">α</span></span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"The trivial constructor; carries no information. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted.mk","kind":"ctor","line":41,"name":"ProofWanted.mk","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L41-L44"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">structure</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted\"><span class=\"name\">ProofWanted</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">α</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Sort</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Wrapper recording that a `proof_wanted` of statement `α` has been declared. ","docLink":"./Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.html#ProofWanted","kind":"structure","line":41,"name":"ProofWanted","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/batteries/blob/77d3cc514f987c1f42f2bbd8a8d56855012dc115/Batteries/Util/ProofWanted.lean#L41-L44"}}],"imports":["Batteries.Lean.Syntax","Batteries.Tactic.Lint.Misc","Init","Lean.Elab.Command","Lean.Elab.Term","Lean.Meta.Tactic.TryThis"],"instances":[],"name":"Batteries.Util.ProofWanted"}